</廢止註記>
<沿革內容><![CDATA[1. Enacted and Promulgated 15 sections by Ministry of National Defense on April 13,  1981.
2. Amended and promulgated 15 sections by Ministry of National Defense on August 5 in 1988.
3. Amended and promulgated 11 sections by Ministry of National Defense on December  30, 2000( original appellation: The Rules of Organization regulations of the Military Police Command).
   Be determined by the Executive Yuan,the act shall be put into practice from the date of December 24, 2001.
4. Article 3,4,7,11 and organization chart amended and promulgated by Ministry of National Defense on May 18, 2004; the regulations will be put into practice from the promulgation date.]]></沿革內容>
<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Regulation is enacted in accordance with Paragraph 1 of Article 10 of the Organization Act of the Ministry of National Defense（MND）.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The Military Police Command of MND (hereinafter referred to as MPC) administers overall military police affairs and takes responsibility for commanding and supervising its subordinate command and field units.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The MPC has authorities over the following affairs:
1. Planning, supervision, and implementation of political warfare affaires.
2. Planning, supervision, and implementation of Inspectoral and Legal affaires.
3. Planning, supervision, and implementation of personnel management, education, historic management and general administrations.
4. Planning, supervision, and implementation of military police intelligence operation and criminal investigation.
5. Planning, supervision, and implementation of combat, garrison, mobilization and training.
6. Planning, supervision, and implementation of logistic.
7. Planning, supervision, and implementation of communication and information.
8. Planning and supervision of military force establishment, both policies and developments.
9. Planning and supervision of budget, accounting, and statistics.
10. Planning, supervision, and implementation  of other affaire .
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The MPC has several units, including Political Director General's Office, Inspector General's Office, Personnel and General Affairs Division, Intelligence Division, Operations Division, Logistics Division, Communications and information Division,Planning Division, and Comptroller Division. These units are responsible for the affairs listed above and  may be established according to their functions and requirements.
Within the stipulated personnel quota of this regulation, the MND may based in military requirements, add or reduce the above units or establish other units.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[In order to meet the requirements of military police operations and force buildup, the MPC may establish command, training, professional, implementing, supporting, and R & D units as well as combat troops. The organization of the aforementioned units should be stipulated by a table of organization and equipment.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The MPC has one Commanding General and one Deputy Commanding General, whose ranks are both Lieutenant General.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The MPC places the Chief of Staff, Political Warfare Director, Inspector-General, Vice Chief of Staff, Deputy Political Warfare Director, Director, Deputy Inspector-General, Deputy Director , Chief, Chief Aide-de-Camp, Director, Deputy Chief, staff, Deputy Director.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The grades and quota of various titles at this regulation should be stipulated by another organization table.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 9</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The detailed description of the authority and responsibilities of various levels at this regulation should be stipulated by another table.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 10</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The MPC may, based on its requirements, hire 5-7 advisers and civilian employees.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 11</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Regulation in additional to be amended and promulgated on  Dec.30, 2000 and should be put into force from the date of March 1,2002; the amended articles  will be put into practice from the promulgation date.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
</法規>
